\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {29}{\ignorespaces Linear OT coordinates. Fixing a reference measure $\rho $ turns each target into the displacement field $T_\alpha -\mathrm  {Id}$. In one dimension this is exactly the quantile parametrization of $\Wass  _2$, so averaging displacement fields gives the true Wasserstein barycenter. In two dimensions the same construction averages Brenier maps from a central Gaussian reference toward two multimodal targets; it is a tangent approximation and should not be confused with the generally nonlinear Wasserstein barycenter.}}{52}{figure.7.29}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:dualnorms-linear-ot-embedding}{{29}{52}{Linear OT coordinates. Fixing a reference measure $\rho $ turns each target into the displacement field $T_\alpha -\Id $. In one dimension this is exactly the quantile parametrization of $\Wass _2$, so averaging displacement fields gives the true Wasserstein barycenter. In two dimensions the same construction averages Brenier maps from a central Gaussian reference toward two multimodal targets; it is a tangent approximation and should not be confused with the generally nonlinear Wasserstein barycenter}{figure.7.29}{}}
