\newlabel{fig:dualnorms-phi-generators}{{30}{55}{$\phi $-divergences through density ratios. The left panel shows normalized generators for common divergences as functions of $s=\d \alpha /\d \beta $; all curves vanish at $s=1$ up to affine normalization. The right panel shows the discrete formula $D_\phi (a|b)=\sum _i b_i\phi (a_i/b_i)$: hollow blue circles encode $b_i$, filled red circles encode $a_i$, the violet curve gives the ratios $a_i/b_i$, and orange lollipops show local KL-type contributions}{figure.7.30}{}}
